ri Sri Chandi path***. Thus tradition holds that one needs to be initiated =
to chant it. However if one
 wishes to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sac=
red myth aspects of the Devi Mahatmyam, , reading the sacred myth in the ve=
rnacular has been recommended in my write-up, as chanting the original alon=
g with the navakshari amounts to practicing the sadhana of a Mahavidya. In =
that case it is recommended to be initiated and go through the specialised =
sadhanas properly under guidance.<BR><BR>8. Arguably if an uninitiated pers=
on reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the original Sanskrit as part of the *Pauran=
ik* approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an inherent problem in our time=
s. The problem with attempting to do a parayana of Devi Mahatmyam from text=
s alone (without initiation) is that most readers inadvertently end up also=
 chanting the Navarna mantra or stotras such as the Siddhakunjika stotram w=
hich too contain the bijaksharas.<BR><BR>9. I you carefully peruse my write=
-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget translating, nowhere do I put down the Na=
varna mantra even in
 writing. Neither have I attempted to write a commenta=
ry on it. Translations of mantras do not have the power of the original man=
tra as Sabda or Vak. However it is recommended to know the essence or impor=
t (artha) of the mantra and its sadhana while chanting it. Infact `artha' i=
s the import, the essence of `Vak', not a translation! <BR><BR>10. For thos=
e who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path without initiation, there is no=
 need to worry or be confused. There has to be a certain level of samskara =
to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We all have it. Otherwise we=
 would not be doing it (initiation or no initiation). Please keep doing wha=
tever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do sakama sadhana. As Narasimh=
a garu has rightly pointed out it is better to just do the sadhana WITHOUT =
asking for any favours or results. That attitude itself will reduce a lot o=
f the potential problem. Things will happen on their own accord in the natu=
ral flow.
